    "This can imprint a redshift-dependent bias on the source distribution that is localised in particular areas on-sky.",
    "Such a selection bias is problematic for (primarily) photometric clustering studies, but also for cosmic shear (albeit at higher order) as it exacerbates variable depth (see e.g.",
